Useful for injecting API docs into project README files. ## Synopsis 1\. Document your code using valid jsdoc comments. ```js /** * A quite wonderful function. * @param {object} - privacy gown * @param {object} - security * @returns {survival} */ function protection (cloak, dagger) {} ``` 2\. Run a command. ```sh $ jsdoc2md example.js ``` 3\. Get markdown output. ```markdown ## protection(cloak, dagger) survival A quite wonderful function. **Kind**: global function | Param | Type | Description | | ------ | ------------------- | ------------ | | cloak | object | privacy gown | | dagger | object | security | ``` ## Install ``` $ npm install -g jsdoc-to-markdown ``` ## See also * [API documentation](https://github.com/jsdoc2md/jsdoc-to-markdown/blob/master/docs/API.md) * The [wiki](https://github.com/jsdoc2md/jsdoc-to-markdown/wiki) for example output, FAQs, tutorials, plugins, use with gulp/grunt etc. * * * © 2014-19 Lloyd Brookes <75pound@gmail.com>.

Useful for injecting API docs into project README files. ## Synopsis 1\. Document your code using valid jsdoc comments. ```js /** * A quite wonderful function. * @param {object} - Privacy gown * @param {object} - Security * @returns {survival} */ function protection (cloak, dagger) {} ``` 2\. Run a command. ```sh $ jsdoc2md example.js ``` 3\. Get markdown output. ```markdown ## protection(cloak, dagger) survival A quite wonderful function. **Kind**: global function | Param | Type | Description | | ------ | ------------------- | ------------ | | cloak | object | Privacy gown | | dagger | object | Security | ``` ## Install ``` $ npm install --save-dev jsdoc-to-markdown ``` ## See also * [API documentation](https://github.com/jsdoc2md/jsdoc-to-markdown/blob/master/docs/API.md) * The [wiki](https://github.com/jsdoc2md/jsdoc-to-markdown/wiki) for example output, FAQs, tutorials, plugins, use with gulp/grunt etc. * * * © 2014-24 Lloyd Brookes \<75pound@gmail.com\>.
